Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Princeton Lee Witherspoon

records.addlTxt: No contact with Super One Stores, Ace Hardware, SH or JP

AND BAIL/BOND HEARING 11:00 AM Defendant Princeton Lee Witherspoon in court.  Attorney Joseph Foster Rosenthal in court for Princeton Lee Witherspoon.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Rosenthal received information, waives reading and pleads not guilty. Court accepts not guilty plea. Attorney Rosenthal asks for a signature bond for defendant to be released to treatment. Attorney Rosenthal attached admission letter with motion filed. State opposed to bail modification and finds cash bail necessary. Since 2009, defendant has more than 40 failures to appear and 15 probation violations. State asks if bail is modified asks that cash be ordered. Attorney Rosenthal states some money has been posted in another case. Court reviews defendant's other pending charge. Court reviews this offense occurred days after posting bail in another case. Court increases bail to $5,000 cash with same conditions of no contact with Super One stores, Ace Hardware, SH or JP.
Status conference scheduled for November 28, 2022 at 11:00 am.

records.addlTxt:
10:09 AM Defendant Princeton Lee Witherspoon in court, in custody.  Attorney Joseph Foster Rosenthal in court for Princeton Lee Witherspoon.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. State calls Detective Sean Holmgren. Detective Holmgren sworn and testified. State direct examination of Detective Holmgren. State submits Exhibits #1-Photo of transaction with defendant and #2 Photo of defendant. Court receives Exhibits #1 and #2. Witness identifies the defendant. State submits Exhibit #3 - Photo of defendant by surveillance at Super One. Court receives Exhibit #3. Attorney Rosenthal cross examines Detective Holmgren. State makes argument for bind over. Attorney Rosenthal makes argument in opposition. Court finds probable cause and binds the defendant over for arraignment. Court sets arraignment.
Arraignment scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 11:00 am.
Defendant's Demand for Discovery and Inspection
records.descr: Demand for Discovery and Inspection - Defendant

records.addlTxt: No contact with Super One Stores, Ace Hardware Store, SH or JP.

1:47 PM Defendant Princeton Lee Witherspoon appeared by video, in custody.  Prosecuting attorney Peter James Marvin Kruger in court for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman appeared by video for Princeton Lee Witherspoon. Defendant's address confirmed. Defendant advised of right to consult an attorney and options for counsel. Defendant would like public defender to make special appearance. Attorney/Defendant acknowledges receipt of the complaint, waives a formal reading, enters pleas of not guilty to the misdemeanor count(s), and requests a preliminary hearing. State asks for $5000 cash. No contact with Super One Stores, Ace Hardware, Samantha Hall or Jenna Peterson. State notes over 40 FTAs across a long criminal history in MN and WI. Attorney Hoffman notes that defendant is lifelong resident of Duluth with family in the area. Defendant notes that he has full custody of his daughter due to her mother's recent passing and has recently made recent court appearances. Notes he would like to get case resolved. Notes that he was in court as recently as yesterday. Attorney Hoffman notes that he has made recent court appearances in other pending matters. Defendant can post up to $500.
Court notes concerns over significant criminal history and FTAs. 
Court orders $3,000 cash bail. No contact with Super One Stores, Ace Hardware, SH, or JP.
Attorney Hoffman notes that Attorney Rosenthal will be appointed on this matter.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 5, 2022 at 10:00 am.
